  "prompt": "Who are IAS Aspirants?",
  "response": "IAS aspirants are individuals preparing for the Indian Administrative Service (IAS) examination, which is part of the Civil Services Examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in India. The IAS is one of the three All India Services, along with the Indian Police Service (IPS) and Indian Forest Service (IFoS), and it is highly prestigious and competitive.\n\nAspirants typically come from diverse educational backgrounds and may include recent graduates, working professionals, and sometimes even individuals who have been preparing full-time. Their goal is to secure a high rank in the UPSC exams, which allows them to be selected for the IAS, where they can serve as administrators in various capacities within the government.\n\nThe preparation for the IAS exam is rigorous and involves studying a wide range of subjects, including history, geography, politics, economics, science, technology, environment, ethics, and current affairs, among others. Candidates often enroll in coaching classes, participate in study groups, and engage in self-study to cover the extensive syllabus. The exam itself consists of three stages: the Preliminary Examination, the Main Examination, and the Personality Test (Interview).",
